> "Are you alright?"Lunarpine asked with more concern in his voice than
> he'd origionally intended."Are you able to fly?"
>
> He helped Shadow Wing to her feet (Talons) and checked her wing.
> Nothing appearedto be damaged beyond internal repair capabilities.
>
> He looked in her great owl eyes and saw the beast she could've been
> if she wasn't a transformer. A spark which seemed to be wanting
> completion. He kissed the top of her beak and brushed his hand
> through her soft downy feathers.
>
> Unfortunately Lunarpine didn't know when to shut up."See I told you
> not to worry about my eyes."
>
>  --- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, logomorph@h... wrote:
> > ::Shadow Wing::
> >
> > She slowly opened her eyes.  Lunarpine had her wing pinned to the
> > ground.  She turned her head to see the tree had fallen next to
> her.
> > She turned back to look at Lunarpine. She was slightly dazed by the
> > fall but assest the situation quickly.  With her wing pinned, he
> won
> > this round. She sighed, "You win this round beloved." She raised
> her
> > head and lightly touched her beak to his nose.
